caption: Hands down the best sushi in Cleveland!!!
Great Sushi

Really good sushi. I ordered a delivery and it all came in cardboard boxes and were separately packed with extra little containers for soy sauce and extra chopsticks! For me that was a win because most other places just shove all the sushis into one plastic box! I really loved the flavors and would definitely recommend!
Great happy hour!
Beautiful place and very friendly environment!!
Decent sushi. Went for the uni but they didn't have it.

Best sushi in Cleveland, and great low key ambiance. Though they can do that too, it doesn't default to as fancy as some of the other "best" places, it's just super high quality food in a warm friendly spot.
Surprisingly affordable for great sushi and service. Stellar location. Why are you waiting in line at the taco shack?? Head next door to Sushi 86!

So tasty! I really enjoyed the scallop six piece roll but the hilariously named 3way reverse cowgirl was the real star of the show for me. Make sure to save room for mochi! The Thai tea flavor is amazing! The drink menu is unique too. Definitely worth checking out.
Great service and better food!
Hell of a Surprise Great Sushi!!!!!
Love this place!!! Quite authentic Japanese food and for a fair price. Love the vegetarian options and very appreciative of them. Cant wait to try the authentic mochi dessert next time!!
Good food, reasonably fast, friendly. Quiet on a weeknight. Enjoyed all the rolls we got.

I ordered the shrimp and avocado roll and added cucumber (no additional charge), and my fiancé ordered the salmon and avocado roll. Service was fast, and the food was good for being inexpensive. High quality interior of the restaurant.
(Translated by Google) Tasty but expensive  (Original) טעים אבל יקר
Great laid back place! Amazing sushi, and great employees. Definitely try the 3-way reverse cowgirl.

Came across this place on a trip to the House of Blues and had the best sushi I have ever eaten. I would recommend the 3 Way Reverse Cowgirl roll! Awesome name and even better taste. The sushi chef was a very personable dude too.
Fish quality was excellent. Reasonably priced. Friendly staff. Clean modern interior.
The cowgirl sushi is one of my favorite dishes at this restaurant. Good food for a decent price 👍

Ate here before a Cavs game. The restaurant is literally right across the road from the Arena. Its a family run place. I ate at the bar and chatted to one of the owners who was also the sushi chef. Service was excellent and the food came …

I door dash and the ladies who brought the order for me made comments about how I walk because I have a disability and how I shouldn't be allowed to handle food because of it. Very disrespectful and discriminating

I keep telling people that Sushi 86 *might* be my favorite sushi place in Cleveland.  It *might* be time for me to just admit that it *is* my favorite.  I kinda miss the styling of the old location, though.
Spectacular sushi 👌
Great sushi. Kind of hidden. For those looking, it is INSIDE of the Arcades on 5th. Pretty cozy. Friendly staff. Would recommend.

The sushi was really good and restaurant was clean. We went on a Saturday night around 6:30 and we were the only people there. It's hidden inside the arcade but was worth the hunt. They have a good selection of non seafood rolls for those friends of yours that don't like seafood. The prices are great too!
Wonderful sushi experience. Excellent mixing of flavors. Decor is tasteful as well. Sit at the bar and watch the show.
Always fresh and tasty fish here. Always good to come here for happy hour on weekdays.
Amazing! The food and staff were perfect. I will definitely be coming back!
Enjoy this place every time I come great owner/chef, great fish. My second favorite sushi spot in Cleveland.
THE BEST. The sushi is always super fresh and always hits the spot. Very quick service on your lunch hour. Their new space makes the atomosphere and whole dining experience a 10/10.
Great food, not the largest menu.
Delicious
I love this place! The sushi is always so fresh, I have never been disappointed. So many fancy sushi places in Cleveland but this hidden spot is my favorite.
Hands down best Sushi in town. Very personable owners!
Great design, great service tasty sushi
The staff was very pleasant and the sushi delicious. Nice quiet location.
Great sushi and the people are so welcoming.
Overall best sushi in Cleveland. Fish is always excellent quality. Price is reasonable for sushi. Excellent for gluten free. Highly recommend.
I never had eaten or like sushi until I met the staff and owner of this restaurant great people great place
This is the best sushi place in Cleveland area. Period!

Sushi 86 was amazing!! My son and I went to Cleveland to celebrate the end of his freshman year of high school.. we both love sushi .. and 86 did not disappoint! I recommend the tuna jalapeño roll!!! Sit at the sushi bar.. it’s such a great experience!!
Amazing service was not disappointed had a great conversation with Sushi Chef and service was on point. Would recommend.

Walked here after a conference, since someone else had been in the past and said it was good at the time. It was still good when we went, and we had great service and solid food for an acceptable price.
Waitress is nice.  Food was made fast.  Can't complain.  They gave me decent size food portions.
Been eating here for years... best in Cleveland
Wasn't crowded, good service and food. Would go back.

The server was knowledgeable and helpful with the menu and recommendations.  She brought us what we needed promptly and the food was yummy! She got us what we needed without hovering or interrupting our experience.

(Translated by Google) The first dinner on a business trip. Very delicious sushi. I ordered four different rolls, which are quite delicious. Gomoku roll is super delicious. Veggie roll is not bad. I will be patronized again during this week.  (Original) 来出差的第一顿晚餐。很美味的寿司。点了四种不同的roll,都还挺好吃的。Gomoku roll超级好吃。veggie roll也不错。在这呆一周还会再光顾的。
Nothing to brag about at all boring
Best sushi in Cleveland
Great service and food.
Awesome little spot in downtown Cleveland.  Salmon Nigiri served with the subtlest hint of lemon....brilliant!
Best traditional sushi and poke bowls. I pay $20 for parking just to get sushi here. The seaweed salad is great as are the pickled veggies.
Try "the other roll"! I dont think it is on the menu but its the best
John was great.

This place is amazing, both times I've gone I've gotten multiple rolls, but 3 way reverse cowgirl both times 🤯. All the food was delicious &  the staff was very friendly & helpful, can't wait to go back!
First time eating sushi and I will say its damn good! Best one for me was the tuna rolls and miso soup. Will be a regular here sometime in the future!
Friendly service and wonderful food priced appropriately.
My favorite Sushi spot! Yum! Rainbow roll is to die for!
By far my favorite place to eat Sushi. Ben is the best and I love their addition to veterinarian and vegan options!

An excellent location for Sushi. This place serves both American style sushi, but also Japanese style sushi (like sashimi) as well. The establishment is clean and well kept, and the staff are friendly. The dessert menu also features ice cream mochi balls, which aren't too common to find.
Good service, Good food and the owners were very friendly too. Definitely a place to tou will enjoy.

I had the pleasure of finding this gem while in Cleveland for work.  It may be a little hard to find as it is not right on the street, but it is worth the extra effort to find!  Nice atmosphere, great chef and hostess with some of the best sushi I have had.  I will be stopping in on my next visit to Cleveland without a doubt.
Everytime I am in town this is a must stop. Amazing sushi and so many choices.
Fantastic sushi
Not the biggest I've had but tasty and a decent choice of vegetarian options!
Amazing food, amazing staff, amazing atmosphere.  Very on top of everything and super personable.  Wonderful place.
This restaurant delivers consistently high quality sushi and service. The staff is attentive and kind. And like I said, the foods not only good but consistent.
I adore the rather elegant ambience I feel going here. It´s a very calm atmosphere with some amazing sushi prepared right in front of you. It´s also not expensive.
Nice atmosphere you can 👀 your sushi being made no matter where you sit. Great place for lunch downtown cleveland! Reasonably priced!

One of my favorite lunch spots; also great for dinner. Excellent happy hour deals as well, though the prices are so reasonable you should definitely not wait for the specials. Everything tastes wonderful and the staff are friendly and …
Amazing!! Favorite was definitely the 3-Way Reverse Cowgirl!
Gluten Free Poke!!
Great service
The sashimi is really fresh , go for the chef specialty

What a cool little atmosphere Sushi 86 has to offer. It doesn't look like much from the outside but this place blew me away with their selection and the taste was tops. Couldn't have asked for a better surprise than what Sushi 86 provided. Along with that, the price was reasonable too!
Great rolls and hospitality.  Thanks Ben.  Highly recommended.   Try the 3-Way Reverse Cowgirl.
Love the sweet potato sushi
What you would expect from a great sushi bar!
Great sushi, service, and atmosphere at a very reasonable price compared to most sushi restaurants. However, the restaurant itself is a bit difficult to find.

I’ve lived in Japan & learned to prepare sushi there. I was the Executive Chef of the City Club of Cleveland, as well as 3 other restaurants. This is the best sushi you will find in the Cleveland area. Period!
Great customer service
Very good food
Not too bad, wouldn't be my first choice. The seaweed salad was very bland.

Broadest vegan sushi menu on this continent, I swear (alongside more traditional rolls, too). Unfortunately, they always seem to be closed whenever I stop by - they're always hosting on-site events - but I'll keep trying.
Nice relaxing space. Great food and fun sushi combos.
Only have been here once but it was a great experience! Staff kept trying to upsell me on sake when they didn't know what it was but I did so it worked out.
Great choices I wish they had more dessert options
Yum sushi
This is the worst sushi joint in North East Ohio. The service is incredibly slow and food is very bland.
Bland sushi and disgusting sake. Not sure why this place is getting good reviews. There are so many better sushi places in Cleveland. Sad that I wasted my night here.
Amazing!!!
Great!

It took 20 minutes for the employees to ask for my order on a night that was not that busy, then it took another 20 minutes to for them to make a mediocre roll. The rolls were very small compared to other sushi places I have been too and …
3 way reverse cowgirl. Great service and cool little spot conveniently located. If ever back in Cleveland I will be back here!

Don't go there if you want authentic Japanese food. The udon noodle soup have very little soup in it. And the taste is like instant noodles to me. Sushi is below average. Over-priced and the service is sooo slow.
Unassuming, but fantastic quality and value. Friendly service.

Boom!  Where do I begin?  Their menu is easy for gluten-free -- orange dot for items they can make special on request.  The Sho Chiku Bai sake bottle was inexpensive for a good semi-dry, cold, unfiltered sake.  Their sushi86 roll was perfect, too.  This hit the spot after a long week.
Sushi was fresh and good variety but service was average.

Really good sushi and this is from a family that was in Japan for several years.  The restaurant staff was very friendly, the service great and sushi fantastic. Big plus is they are absolutely spot on with taking care of gluten free …
Some of the best sushi I've had!
Good food, great staff.  Been going here for years.  Highly recommend.
Amazing sushi. Reverse cowgirl is the best.

Nice dine-in atmosphere outside 5th Street Arcades. Impressive presentation and quality. The fifth star comes from them boxing up my leftover sushi after dining in and including a napkin, soy sauce, chopstix, and saran wrap over top within the box. I'd say that's the extra mile. Will revisit.
Everytime I go downtown, this place is a must go to spot. Great 🍣
Insanely good, and cheap for what you're getting.
Sushi is pretty good here, I especially like the shrimp tempura rolls.  Decent sake selection and fast service.

Honestly the best sushi in the cleveland area. Family owned and such friendly and amazing staff. Quick service and a modern atmosphere. I work a double shift and will drive all the way from brecksville to downtown when there is a game just for this sushi!!!

Straight across from Quicken Loans Arena.  Quality cuts of fish and Happy Hour specials.  The Sushi Mix dinner was  chefs choice. I had salmon and tuna, white tuna, shrimp, and octopus topped with a sauce.  The white tuna surprised me most of all. It was extra fresh.  The octopus was almost as impressive. One of the best I've had.
Very fresh sushi located in the middle of downtown. This place is very popular for takeout and has limited seating for lunch. Expect a long wait here. I recommend calling in ahead of time.

I had the Chirashi and some nigiri.  I asked to sub whitefish for Hamachi, which they did with a smile (big points).  I was hoping to sub out tuna but was convinced otherwise by my server, and I was glad for it.  I normally find tuna pretty …
I have zero complaints. It was fantastic!
Good sushi rolls
Sushi was great. They serve an special ice cream as a desert which was amazing. The staff were so friendly as well.
Best sushi in Cleveland, I had a reverse cowgirl 3-way while I was there among other things. I promise you won't be disappointed.

I went for lunch and had an experience that was mediocre at best. Sushi was reasonably priced, but poorly prepared. Not sure if lunch staff differs from evening, but the sashimi was sliced entirely too thick. Clearly the owners are cashing …

Great place...

Great sushi, came in for lunch and crushed 3 rolls. Rice was so fresh and so was the tuna. Highly recommended.
Great sushi.  Nice staff.  Restaurant space is small and contemporary.
Really great food. Would not have expected such a small place has such awesome products!

I was just going to do takeout and noticed their cute patio. They quickly replated everything for me and served me on the patio even though they had made my order to go. The food was delicious! At the end of my meal they brought me green tea ice cream wich was terrific. I will definitely come here again next time I am in town.
Best sushi in Cleveland area, but their weekend hours are absolutely terrible. We never get to go because they are always closed.
Great sushi... and, Japanese whiskey.   Thanks
Super good sushi
Loved the eel
The best in CLE, no doubt.

Sushi 86 was a great place to visit i had the 3 way reverse cowgirl and Tempura Roll. i actually liked the Tempura Roll better I think it was because it was more simple with a great flavor. The key to great sushi to me is the rice and this …

I didn't know what to think when I waked in. Not your typical sushi joint. However, we were pleasantly surprised how fresh the sushi tasted and the service was great! I recommend this spot to anyone who is a enjoys sushi. Sushi 86 is great!
Fantastic!
the sushi at Univ. Hosp. cafeteria was very good, but not enough soy sauce.  Especially not enough on the larger package.  Please put more soy sauce into the package.  Thanks.
Amazing sushi!! Good sake too

The sushi was so exceptional...I haven't had better anywhere in Ohio or anywhere else! They toasted the nori so well and the sushi rice was perfect! But the quality of the raw fish and seafood was so outstanding! Please people, check this …
The only sushi place that I would visit again.  Not really a fan of sushi but I love this place.  Have no idea why.

GREAT sushi!!!  We came in on a Friday night, and had a bit of a wait from when we ordered to when we got our food, otherwise I'd give them five full stars, but the sushi was TOTALLY worth the wait!  I highly recommend dropping in here if you have time!!

I went here for lunch a couple days ago and I have to say I was quite impressed. I ordered the miso soup, tuna sashimi and a couple specialty rolls and was impressed with the quality of the sushi. The service was good, although the inside …
Everything here is FANTASTIC! I don't like getting sushi from anywhere else! The staff and the food are unbeatable.

My little hidden gem.. family owned..super sweet service! Always very friendly and happy to have my family in there for dinner. I tried something new and used them for catering for an open house.. just to be clear it was a small open house..but it was a hit and affordable.

Though I am an admitted sushi novice / simpleton, I thought Sushi86 was as good as I could hope for, especially for a noob. John was most helpful explaining to me and my family what we were ordering. Good food, made fresh, tasted great!  I'll go there again when I'm in the area!
